@endnode

@node "The_Naked_Time" "The Naked Time"

                                 Episode #006
                               @{b}@{i}THE NAKED TIME @{ub}@{ui}
                                @{fg fill}John F. Black@{fg text}
                         @{fg shine}Original Air Date: 09-29-66@{fg text}
                          Director: Marc Daniels 

   While in danger of crashing into a planet with unstable gravity, the whole
 crew is infected with a virus that releases inhibitions and reduces men to
 children playing out fantasies: Sulu attacks in Samuri fashion; Spock hides
 helpless, weeping; Christine Chapel becomes a seductress; and Kirk is off 
 in a romantic daze. McCoy must find an antidote to bring them to their
 senses before they collide with the disintegrating planet.

 @{fg fill}GUEST CAST
 ==========@{fg text}

 Riley...Bruce Hyde                              Dr. Harrison...John Bellah
 Tormolen...Stewart Moss

 @{" MARK " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx The_Naked_Time TOS mark"} @{"UNMARK" system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx The_Naked_Time unmark"} @{" VIEW " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx view"} @{" WIPE " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx clear"}

@endnode

@node "Charlie_X" "Charlie X"

                                 Episode #007
                                  @{b}@{i}CHARLIE X @{ub}@{ui}
               @{fg fill}D.C. Fontana, from a story by Gene Roddenberry@{fg text}
                         @{fg shine}Original Air Date: 09-15-66@{fg text}
                         Director: Lawrence Dobkin 

    An immature adolescent, Charlie, has a need to be loved, a longing for 
 other humans (he was raised by computers), and a psychic power to cause
 almost limitless death and destruction if he doesn't if he doesn't get
 his way. The last time he felt betrayed, he destroyed the star ship Antaries.
 And now he hero-worships Kirk and has a powerful crush on Yoeman Rand.

 @{fg fill}GUEST CAST
 ==========@{fg text}

 Charlie...Robert Walker, Jr.            Thalasian...Abraham Sofaer
 Tina Lawten...Patricia McNulty          Captian Remart...Charles J. Stewart
 Tom Nellis...Dallas Mitchell

 @{" Episode Pic " system "VT TrekGuide:TrekPics/EP007"}

