@node "Dagger_of_the_Mind" "Dagger of the Mind"

                                 Episode #010
                             @{b}@{i}DAGGER OF THE MIND @{ub}@{ui}
                              @{fg fill}Shimon Wincelberg@{fg text}
                         @{fg shine}Original Air Date: 11-03-66@{fg text}
                        Director: Vincent McEveety

  On what Kirk assumes will be a routing inspection of the psychiatric ward
 of Tantalus V penal colony, it is discovered that the director, Dr. Adams,
 is keeping the peace through the use of a "neural neutralizer"--a brain
 wiping machine. Power-mad, the doctor lures Kirk into the fatal device.

 @{fg fill}GUEST CAST
 ==========@{fg text}  

 Dr. Tristan Adams...James Gregory           Dr. Van Gelder...Morgan Woodward
 Dr. Helen Noel...Marianna Hill              Lethe...Suzanne Wilson

 @{" MARK " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx Dagger_of_the_Mind TOS mark"} @{"UNMARK" system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx Dagger_of_the_Mind unmark"} @{" VIEW " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx view"} @{" WIPE " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx clear"}

@endnode

@node "Miri" "Miri"

                                 Episode #011
                                    @{b}@{i}MIRI @{ub}@{ui}
                                @{fg fill}Adrian Spies@{fg text}
                         @{fg shine}Original Air Date: 10-27-66@{fg text}
                        Director: Vincent McEveety

   Anyone over the age of puberty on this earthlike planet fall victim to a
 fatal, leprous disease; but the children age so slowly that they don't know
 why there are no longer any grown-ups ("grups") and why occasionally their
 older members contract the disease and die. They take perpetual childhood
 for granted. The Enterprise officers land and contract the disease--and must
 find corrective and immunization measure but the kids distrust them and 
 sabotage their experiments. Kirk tries to win them over through a young
 girl, Miri, who, entering puberty and contracting the disease, has a crush
 on the Captian.

 @{fg fill}GUEST CAST
 ==========@{fg text}  

 Miri...Kim Darby                        Jahn...Michael J. Pollard
 Ferrell...Jim Goodwin

 @{" Episode Pic " system "VT TrekGuide:TrekPics/EP011"}

 @{" MARK " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx Miri TOS mark"} @{"UNMARK" system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx Miri unmark"} @{" VIEW " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx view"} @{" WIPE " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx clear"}

@endnode

@node "Conscience_of_the_King" "Conscience of the King"

                                 Episode #012
                         @{b}@{i}THE CONSCIENCE OF THE KING  @{ub}@{ui}
                                @{fg fill}Barry Trivers@{fg text}
                        @{fg shine}Original Air Date: 12-08-66@{fg text}
                           Director: Gerd Oswald

   Kirk is given reason to suspect that the leader of a troupe of actors is
 actually a mass murderer, Kodos the executioner, and he beam the troupe aboard
 the Enterprise to study them, as he is one of only three surviving witnesses
 who might identify Kodos. one of the other witnesses is killed, another 
 poisoned. . .and Kirk still isn't certain.

 @{fg fill}GUEST CAST
 ==========@{fg text}

 Anton Karidian...Arnold Moss                    Lenore...Barbara Anderson
 Kevin Riley...Bruce Hyde                        Lt. Leslie...Eddie Paskey

  

