@node "Galileo_Seven" "Galileo Seven"

                                 Episode #013
                                @{b}@{i}GALILEO SEVEN @{ub}@{ui}
                       @{fg fill}Oliver Crawford & S. Bar-David@{fg text}
                         @{fg shine}Original Air Date: 01-05-67@{fg text}
                           Director: Robert Gist

   The shuttlecraft Galileo, with Spock in command, goes out to gather data
 on the quasar-like phenomenoa, Murasaki 312, and is forced to land on planet
 Tarus II for repairs. The Enterprise can't find them due to the quasar's 
 interference with the ships instruments, and it seems there's no chance 
 of rescue or survival for the landing party, which has encountered monstrous
 seven foot natives.

 @{fg fill}GUEST CAST
 ==========@{fg text}

 Boma...Don Marshall                       Gaetano...Peter Marko
 Latimer...Rees Vaughn                     Kelowitz...Grant Woods
 Mears...Phillis Douglas                   Commissioner Ferris...John Crawford

 @{" MARK " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx Galileo_Seven TOS mark"} @{"UNMARK" system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx Galileo_Seven unmark"} @{" VIEW " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx view"} @{" WIPE " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx clear"}

@endnode

@node "Court_Martial" "Court Martial"

                                 Episode #014
                                @{b}@{i}COURT MARTIAL @{ub}@{ui}
                  @{fg fill}Don M. Mankiewicz & Stephen W. Carbatsos@{fg text}
                         @{fg shine}Original Air Date: 02/02/67@{fg text}
                          Director: Marc Daniels

  Kirk's career is at stake when he is put on trial for obstruction of 
 justice and culpable negligence, accused of killing a crew member during 
 the panic of an ion storm. The ships computer no only has a record of events
 that prove Kirk's guilt, but can reproduce TV pictures that support the
 record. Kirk's prosecutor is an old flame he fondly remembers; his defender
 is a shrewd cantankerous old coot known for taking hopeless cases.

 @{fg fill}GUEST CAST
 ==========@{fg text}

 Commodore Stone...Percy Rodriguez               Samuel Cogley...Elisha Cook
 Areel Shaw...Joan Marshall                      Finney...Richard Webb
 Jamie Finney...Alice Rawlings                   Hanson...Hagan Beggs
 Timothy...Winston DeLugo

 @{" MARK " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx Court_Martial TOS mark"} @{"UNMARK" system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx Court_Martial unmark"} @{" VIEW " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx view"} @{" WIPE " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx clear"}

@endnode

@node "The_Menagerie_Pt.1" "The Menagerie Pt1"

                                 Episode #015
                             @{b}@{i}THE MENAGERIE PT.1 @{ub}@{ui}
                              @{fg fill}Gene Roddenberry@{fg text}
                         @{fg shine}Original Air Date: 11-17-66@{fg text}
   Director: Marc Daniels (The Cage Segments Directed by Robert Butler)

  In the original Star Trek's only two part story, Spock contrives to
 take over the Enterprise and set her course toward Talos IV, a planet 
 off limits to the Federation, He kidnaps Kirk's predecessor, Captian 
 Pike, and while not relinquishing control of the ship, he turns himself 
 in for court martial and a sure death penalty. Pike is a victim of
 radiation poisoning, and while mentally alert, is physically no more
 than a vegetable. Spock attempts to explain his actions by showing
 visual records of Pike's last visit to Talos IV, where Pike had been
 captured, placed in a zoo, and invited to mate with first one Earth
 woman then another. Part of his tortures consisted of masterful illusions 
 that made him see one woman as many different women (This story is
 an expanded version of the original pilot episode, "The Cage").

 @{fg fill}GUEST CAST
 ========== @{fg text}

 Captian Pike...Jeffrery Hunter                  Jose Mendez...Malcomb Throne
 Vina...Susan Oliver                             Miss Piper...Julia Parrish
 Lt. Hansen...Hagan Beggs                        Tyler...Peter Duryea
 The Keeper...Meg Wylie                          Dr. Boyce...John Hoyt
 Number One...Majel Barrett

 @{" Episode Pic " system "VT TrekGuide:TrekPics/EP015"}

 @{" MARK " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx The_Menagerie_Pt.1 TOS mark"} @{"UNMARK" system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx The_Menagerie_Pt.1 unmark"} @{" VIEW " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx view"} @{" WIPE " system "rx trekguide:Trx/MV.rexx clear"}

@endnode

